<item>
            <title>[LDAP-14] Exceptions not Serializable</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/LDAP-14</link>
                <project id="10071" key="LDAP">Spring LDAP</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hello &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We have a remote service utilizing Spring-Ldap. We&apos;d like to be able to return exceptions to the service caller, however they&apos;re not Serializable &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Perhaps it is the wrapped NamingException that is not Serializable. My preference is for the exceptions to be serializable (perhaps there are other points of view), therefore I&apos;d suggest to wrap the stack trace and message from NamingException and discard the non-Serializable part. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards, &lt;br/&gt;
Jasper&lt;/p&gt;</description>
